{
  "answer": "**The work *Kalpabuddha* (unknown author) dedicates chapters 1–5 to each of the five Tathāgatas (Pañcatathāgata), assigning them these precise internal organs as bodily abodes: Vairocana (chapter 1, heart), Akṣobhya (chapter 2, lungs), Ratnasambhava (chapter 3, spleen), Amitābha (chapter 4, liver), and Amoghasiddhi (chapter 5, gall bladder).**[^1][^2][^3][^4][^5]\n\nEach of these chapters ends with a version of the specified formula. Here are verbatim quotes of the residence-formulas from chapters 1 (Vairocana), 2 (Akṣobhya), and 5 (Amoghasiddhi):\n\n> Now, as for his residence in the body, the inside of the heart is his abode.[^6]\n\n> Now, as for his residence in the body, the inside of the lungs is his abode.[^7]\n\n> Now, as for his residence in the body, the inside of the gall bladder is his abode.[^8]\n\nChapter 3 (Ratnasambhava) ends with the slightly abbreviated: \"The inside of the spleen is his abode.\" Chapter 4 (Amitābha) uses the full formula for the liver.[^9]\n\n[^1]: *Kalpabuddha*, ch. 1, [translation/](/works/unknown-kalpabuddha-d760dc/01/translation/).\n[^2]: *Kalpabuddha*, ch. 2, [translation/](/works/unknown-kalpabuddha-d760dc/02/translation/).\n[^3]: *Kalpabuddha*, ch. 3, [translation/](/works/unknown-kalpabuddha-d760dc/03/translation/).\n[^4]: *Kalpabuddha*, ch. 4, [translation/](/works/unknown-kalpabuddha-d760dc/04/translation/).\n[^5]: *Kalpabuddha*, ch. 5, [translation/](/works/unknown-kalpabuddha-d760dc/05/translation/).\n[^6]: *Kalpabuddha*, ch. 1, [p-e1c8df](/works/unknown-kalpabuddha-d760dc/01/translation/#p-e1c8df).\n[^7]: *Kalpabuddha*, ch. 2, [p-5a580a](/works/unknown-kalpabuddha-d760dc/02/translation/#p-5a580a).\n[^8]: *Kalpabuddha*, ch. 5, [p-8f8def](/works/unknown-kalpabuddha-d760dc/05/translation/#p-8f8def).\n[^9]: *Kalpabuddha*, ch. 3, [p-68d96e](/works/unknown-kalpabuddha-d760dc/03/translation/#p-68d96e); ch. 4, [p-60c6c3](/works/unknown-kalpabuddha-d760dc/04/translation/#p-60c6c3).",
